One week ago we lost our beautiful baby boy Francisquito Fairless-Waterford (2020-2023). He wasn’t here for long, but he brought so much joy into our lives and to others who knew him. We called him “the most loved bulldog” because our love for him was instant and obsessive. We never knew that an animal could change our lives the way that Quito did. 

He loved sleeping all day, eating treats, chewing on his rubber pig toys, cuddling his moms, and generally being extremely lazy. He was a staunch minimalist who barked at anything in our home that was out of place. After trips to the West Hollywood dog park, he always tried to drag us into The Abbey because he thrived on attention and nacho scraps. When we took showers, he sat on the bathmat with his back to us, guarding us. 

When he got sick we prayed for a miracle to save him. We later realized that he was already our miracle. We were his whole world, and we hope he knows that he was ours.
